 This error occurs because you're trying to use the `landscape` environment without loading the necessary package. The `landscape` environment is typically provided by the `pdflscape` or `lscape` package, which you need to include in your document preamble.

To fix this error, add one of the following lines to your document preamble (the area before `\begin{document}`):

```latex
\usepackage{pdflscape}  % Preferred for PDF output
```

OR

```latex
\usepackage{lscape}     % For traditional LaTeX output
```

The `pdflscape` package is generally recommended for modern documents as it works better with PDF output and properly rotates the page in PDF viewers.

If you don't actually need the landscape orientation for a section of your document, you could also simply remove the `\begin{landscape}` and `\end{landscape}` commands from your document.

The full fix would look like this in your preamble:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{amsmath,amssymb,amsfonts,amsthm,physics}
\usepackage{graphicx}
\usepackage{xcolor}
\usepackage{hyperref}
\usepackage{mathtools}
\usepackage{tikz}
\usepackage{pdflscape}  % Add this line to fix the error
\usetikzlibrary{arrows,decorations.markings}
```

After adding this package, the error should be resolved and your document should compile successfully.

